AKURE – Social Democracy Party (SDP) on Saturday swore in all elected party Chairmen and Secretaries across South West states. The event, which took place at the Nigeria Union Of Journalist NUJ press centre, Alagbaka, Akure, the Ondo State capital, saw all the newly elected party Chairmen and Secretaries take oath of office with other elected members of the executives in attendance. Ambassador Oke Idawena, who was the chairman of the occasion, charged the newly inaugurated executives to put in their best in working for the progress of the party. -Advertisement- He said the party’s interest should supersede any personal interest of the members of the executives in all the states. The state Chairman of the party in Ondo State, Hon. Stephen Adewale noted that  the innovations and cooperation of all members of the party made the party’s last Congress a reality and successful. He declared that the party was fully set to accept any political office seekers who have same goal of rescuing the nation from the woods. His Lagos State counterpart, Ms Dabiraoluwa Adeyinka stated that SDP would win substantially in the 2023 general elections. She, therefore, called on the electorate to vote for SDP because it has the best people-oriented manifesto for the people. POLL SDP across states in the South West geopolitical zone on April 9, 2022 held its congress electing their new executive members. Besides the Ondo and Lagos states chairmen, other chairmen sworn in include Yunus Gbadamosi of Osun State, Aderoju Okunlade of Oyo State and Yinka Williams of Ogun State.